    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Eroded Self</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Maria M Guarente supports Jeffrey Rosen's April 30 article on invasion of privacy via Internet</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Jeffrey Rosen's article (April 30) sent chills down my spine as I read it for the second and third times. I have always viewed the Internet as yet another way for the world to invade my privacy. I will not permit anyone to decide what books, movies, Web sites or products will be marketed to me based on a stereotype derived from a machine. A machine cannot evaluate a whim or an emotional purchase. As Rosen so perceptively states, ''Privacy protects us from being misdefined and judged out of context.''</p>
        <p>Maria M. Guarente  Hurley, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
